title: Frank Lloyd Wright Ennis Textile Mini Brick Model
description:
In the early 1920s, Frank Lloyd Wright gave new life to the common concrete block with an innovative building system he called “textile block construction.”

With the Ennis Textile Block set, builders will construct the textile block detail from The Ennis House designed by Wright in 1923 and built by his son Lloyd in 1924. Evoking the look of a Mayan Temple, The Ennis House was the last monumental and complex of the four textile block homes Wright designed in the Los Angeles area.

  • Assembled Dimensions: 8" W x 6.25" L x 2.5" H
